===Noun===
'''psychrometer'''
# A form of [[hygrometer]]. The psychrometer uses the two thermometers, one with a wet fabric sleeve on it.  The two temperature readings, from the [[dry-bulb thermometer]] and the [[wet-bulb thermometer]], can be used to calculate humidity.

To get correct readings, it is necessary to flow air over the wet bulb.  In the most common type of psychrometer, a [[sling psychrometer]], this is achieved by whirling the wet-bulb thermometer around on a sling.  In an [[aspiration psychrometer]], the wet bulb is stationary but air is blown across it.

Source: American Meteorological Society Glossary of Meteorology, http://amsglossary.allenpress.com/glossary/search?id=psychrometer1.
Source: FM 3-6 '''Field Behavior of Chemical, Biological and Radiological Agents'''

